name: Salmon & Zucchini Skewers Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Combine paprika, oregano, 2 tbs oil, zest and lime juice in a bowl. Add salmon and toss to coat.

Place 3 zucchini ribbons on top of each other to form a stack. Repeat with remaining zucchini ribbons. Alternate threading zucchini stacks and salmon onto 12 skewers. Heat a large greased chargrill pan over high heat. Cook skewers, turning, for 6 minutes or until salmon is almost cooked through. Season.
Combine salad leaves, vinegar and remaining oil in a bowl. Season. Serve skewers with tzatziki, salad leaves and extra lime.
